$interpreted: Crushfang: So this is the Kingdom of Sun's genius strategist that the princess told me about? Heard you're Nikola's lone disciple.
Hyde: Greetings. Indeed, my master is...
Dagger: --Hmpf, genius? We'll see about that...
Crushfang: Dagger! Manners!
Crushfang: Princess, the Bears chose to assist you for one purpose; in hopes that after the war finishes,
Crushfang: Bears can return to their previous lifestyle, one where illegal miners don't bother us anymore.
Angelia: Chieftain Crushfang, I understand your concerns. But I have witnessed Sir Hyde's strategic capabilities first-hand.
Angelia: I can assure you that he will lead us to victory against Theodore.
Dagger: Hell no, Angelia. You understand nothing! War is all about life and death.
Dagger: Asking us to hand our lives to this total stranger, a bit sloppy, don't you think?
Dylan: I agree as well.
Angelia: Colonel Levon!?
Dylan: Princess, pardon my intrusion, but war is not child's play. As someone with no actual combat experience, your assurance means little.
Dylan: I've worked with Minister Nikola in the past and acknowledged his abilities, but it's a different story with his disciple, whom I'm unfamiliar with.
Angelia: But...
Hyde: Alright, chill out, everyone. Don't start an argument over little old me.
Hyde: Combat experience, eh? You have a point~ If everyone has their doubts, then how about we fight it out?
Dagger: Hahaha, a fight? With little wimp like you?
Hyde: I mean a simulation battle~
Hyde: I'll be in charge of the Sunshine Infantry; the Bears by a commander of their choice. We'll have a simple skirmish; winner gets the right to command.
Hyde: If you want to test my abilities, this is the simplest way to do so.
Dagger: Hmph, we Bears accept the challenge. Chieftain, what do you say?
Crushfang: Keep things civilized. As long as there are no casualties, I accept.
Dylan: Agreed.
Angelia: If Sir Hyde is okay with it, then I accept it too.
Hyde: Then let us lay down some ground rules~
Dagger: So, any movement from Sunshine Infantry?
Furygrowl: Princess is still defending the main camp, but that Hyde guy has taken a small army himself.
Furygrowl: Seems like he is trying to circle around the forest.
Dagger: Planning sneak attack, are ya...
Dagger: We have advantages in both numbers and terrain. Let's go kick that cocky Hyde's human butt!

Furygrowl: Shouldn't we target the princess while their forces are separated? 

All we need to do is take over the main camp or capture the enemy leader, then we win.
Dagger: Though it's just simulation battle, I don't want to take the risk of injuring Angelia. As long as we get Hyde, Angelia will know that he is not trustworthy.
Dagger: Stop wasting time. Everyone, follow me!
Hyde: Whew~ Expect no less from the Bears' elite. With all of you here, a weakling strategist like me is no match...
Dagger: All alone, separated from your entire unit. Yet you're still laughing.
Dagger: Cut that out, it's irritating me!
Hyde: Hold up. Please maintain this formation. Don't press forward.
Dagger: What, finally getting scared now?
Hyde: No. It's just easier for us to surround you if you don't move.
Dagger: What the...?
Naya: Exactly as Hyde said. All we need to do is set up an ambush here; Dagger will barge in and get himself caught in the trap...
Sione: It's like he can predict the future. Impressive indeed.
Hyde: Good thing that captain Dagger is the commander in charge. If it was Chieftain Crushfang, things might not have gone so smoothly~
Dagger: Whaddaya just say, you stinkin human!?
Hyde: Fellow soldiers, engage with formation two. Take them out swiftly!
Dagger: D-Damn it...
Hyde: This is what I'm capable of. Captain Dagger, do you acknowledge me now?
Dagger: Hmph, a bet's a bet. Go ahead, tell me what you want!
Hyde: I want captain Dagger and all Bear soldiers to follow my orders in the future, no matter what.
Hyde: Any questions?
